    <string name="channel_recovery_info">
        Recovery tool retrieves available channel backups and uses them to reimburse locked funds back into your on-chain wallet.\n\nYou
        should expect a refunding Bitcoin transaction shortly after starting it if you do have lost channels with some locked funds,
        otherwise nothing will happen.\n\nYou are advised to start with this once wallet is fully synchronized.\n\nUsing this tool
        does not affect open channels currently present on this device.
    </string>

    <string name="mnemonic_info">
        <font color="#F00859">Mnemonic phrase is important</font>\n
        <a href="http://lightning-wallet.com/setting-up-bitcoin-wallet#mnemonic-code">Read about it</a> and save it now!
        \n\nYou will need it in case if anything goes wrong with your wallet!
    </string>

    <string name="tokens_warn"><![CDATA[
        Please note: this wallet uses paid <a href=http://lightning-wallet.com/storage-tokens#storage-tokens>storage tokens</a>
        to secure your encrypted channel backups.<br><br>An automatic Lightning payment of <i>%1$s</i> will acquire 50 storage tokens once
        your first channel becomes open.<br><br>These tokens will safeguard you from accidental money loss for the next 50 payment channels.
    ]]></string>

    <string name="zygote_details"><![CDATA[
        Migration tool creates a full snapshot of current wallet state which can be
        used to fully restore your wallet at a later time, possibly on another device.<br><br>
        <strong>Two use cases for this tool</strong><br>
        1. Moving wallet data from one phone to another.<br>
        2. Deleting wallet and restoring it a bit later.<br><br>
        This tool <strong>SHOULD NOT</strong> be used to store a long-term backup of
        your wallet or create multiple copies of the same wallet on many devices!
    ]]></string>

